<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: SHEPPARD M-SERIES - INSPECT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSPECT</title>
        <para>Make a careful visual inspection of all steering gear parts. Replace worn parts as well as any parts that
            show signs of stress or fatigue.
        </para>
        <para>Steering Gear parts inspection may show problems in other areas of the steering system. To avoid repeat
            complaints, inspect all parts carefully. Listed below are the more common complaints you may see during
            steering gear inspection along with their possible cause. This information should be considered carefully
            when repairing low mileage vehicles.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Steering gears that have been damaged in an accident must be replaced. An accident, personal
                    injury or death may result from the failure to do so. Impact loads transmitted through the front
                    axle and steering linkage into the steering gear can stress parts to a point just short of failure.
                    Further use is unsafe and the steering gear assembly and pitman arm must be replaced. Distorted
                    pitman arms, twisted sector shafts, broken or cracked rack and pinion gear teeth are some signs of
                    impact damages. Broken or damaged mounting brackets must be replaced.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <title>Parts Discolored (Blue)</title>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Operating temperatures too high</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Steering column binding</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Hydraulic supply pump malfunctioning.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Broken Housing</title>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Accident damaged</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Housing or Piston Scoring</title>
            (Also see following NOTE)
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Foreign material entry</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Severe overloading</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect lubricant used</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Excessive temperature: over 121 degrees C (250 degrees F)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Pump damaged.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Sector Shaft Roller (Bearing Wear)</title>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect lubricant use</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Excessive temperature</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Overloading the axle</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Contaminated lubricant</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Impact damage.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Actuating Shaft</title>
            (Ball thread brinelled or dented)
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Impact damages</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Thrust Bearings</title>
            (Pitted, Rough)
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Foreign material in system</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Excessive overloading.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Thrust Bearings</title>
            (Broken or Distorted)
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Impact damage</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect repairs.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Actuating Shaft Thread Wear</title>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect lubricant used</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Overloading</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Insufficient operating pressure</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Insufficient oil flow</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Continued operation at high temperature.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <title>Piston Rings Cut, Pinched, Sheared or Worn</title>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect installation</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect assembly.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Scoring, minor scoring and scuffing of the piston and housing of the steering gear is normal.
                    During operation at relatively high pressures and flow rates, this minor scoring will not affect the
                    safety or operation of the steering gear. Minor scoring should be polished with a fine hand stone or
                    crocus cloth.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The cylinder bore should not be honed or bored out as this will increase internal leakage.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
